<h1>Problem 1446 - 2015 USAMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Quadrilateral \(APBQ\) is inscribed in circle \(\omega\) with \(\angle P = \angle Q = 90^{\circ}\) and \(AP = AQ < BP\). Let \(X\) be a variable point on segment \(\overline{PQ}\). Line \(AX\) meets \(\omega\) again at \(S\) (other than \(A\)). Point \(T\) lies on arc \(AQB\) of \(\omega\) such that \(\overline{XT}\) is perpendicular to \(\overline{AX}\). Let \(M\) denote the midpoint of chord \(\overline{ST}\). As \(X\) varies on segment \(\overline{PQ}\), show that \(M\) moves along a circle.</p>
